            "title": "Modern Slavery & Ethical Sourcing Statement"
          }
        },
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "enlarge_text": true,
            "text": "<p>At Hunting Season, we are committed to ensuring that modern slavery, human trafficking, and forced labor have no place in our business or supply chain.</p><p>While we are not legally required under U.S., UK, Australian, or EU thresholds to publish a Modern Slavery Statement at our current scale, we believe in taking responsibility and being transparent as we grow.</p><p>Our products are crafted in small workshops in Colombia and Spain, using responsibly sourced materials including leathers, natural fibers such as Iraca and Fique, and vegetable-ivory Tagua seeds. We also source select materials such as satin and leathers from Italy. We work directly with artisanal cooperatives and family-owned ateliers to maintain close oversight and fair working conditions.</p><p>As a next step, we are developing a Supplier Code of Conduct and strengthening our due diligence processes to increase transparency across our supply chain.</p><p>This statement reflects our commitment to ethical practices and respect for the people and communities who make our collections possible.</p><p>For more information, or to request a copy of our Modern Slavery Statement, please fill out the form below or contact us at support@hunting-season.com</p>"
